VARIABLE WEREDUMBY
NUMBER 2251
NAME Before Grymwood
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
DAY_LIGHT
*DESCRIPTION_START
To the west lies the great beauty sheltered within the mighty Grymwood. To
the east the turbulent waters of the Eltinmar River flow from the mountains
towards the Inner Sea. A small opening, close to the ground, leads into a
small copse of trees, which, while similar to those of the Grymwood, are
different in a way that is hard to discern.  The small copse seems to run
all the way up towards the teeth of Shartan. Mounds of snow slope up to
two openings leading into a copse. Numerous footprints of wolves lead to
one, the other seems less used.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT S 557
ITEM 0 72 ADJ1=294
ITEM 1 72 ADJ1=87
ITEM 9 693
IFPREVERB GO 0
 CLEARVERB
 DISBAND
 IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
  ECHO PLAYER Following the strong call of the small copse you lope into the opening.
  ECHO OTHERS %N disappears into the copse.
  MOVE 2241
  AFFECT 2241
  ECHO OTHERS %N enters the woods.
  AFFECT 2251
 ELSE
  ECHO PLAYER The opening is closed to you.
  ECHO OTHERS %N can not pass through the opening.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 1
 CLEARVERB
 DISBAND
 IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
   IFVAR INTNUM98 > 0
     ECHO PLAYER Following the strong call of the fever of the werewolf inside you, you lope into the opening.
     ECHO OTHERS %N disappears into the copse.
     MOVE 2250
     AFFECT 2250
     ECHO OTHERS %N enters the clearing.
     AFFECT 2251
   ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The thought of passing through that opening brings shudders to your body.
    ECHO OTHERS %N cannot pass through the opening.
   ENDIF
 ELSE
    ECHO PLAYER The opening is closed to you.
    ECHO OTHERS %N cannot pass through the opening.
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
  IFVAR RAC = 4
    PLREVENT 0
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER Your blood stirs as you feel something call to you from inside the copse.
    ECHO OTHERS %N shivers slightly, as if overcome with something.
    PLREVENT 1
    CONTPLREVENT 
    ECHO PLAYER A second, more malevolent odor issues forth from the second opening, turning your skin.
   ENDIF
   IFVAR INTNUM98 > 0
     ECHO PLAYER You scent a dark, welcoming odor coming from the second opening.
  ENDIF
ENDIF
;
NUMBER 2241
NAME Wild Forest
OBSCURED_DAY_LIGHT
CALL 33
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
The stream bed has a trickle of fresh clean water that bubbles
through the clay silt, and small fish swim through its waters.
New young trees have burst forth from the ground below. Winter 
has taken hold, yet the dens seem healthy.  A small hole leads 
out from the copse.
*DESCRIPTION_END
EXIT D 2242
ITEM 0 72 VAL2=2251
ITEM 9 693
IFPREVERB TRANSFORM -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER The Call is too strong here, the wolf blood races like fire through your veins...you decide to keep this form...
ENDIF
IFPREVERB SMELL -1
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER You take a deep breath, and the mild scent of growing things fills your nostrils.
  ECHO OTHERS %N takes a deep breath, and breathes a sigh of relief.
ENDIF
