NUMBER 2245
NAME Ledge
OUTDOOR_OTHER
CALL 33
ASTRAL
*DESCRIPTION_START
Below this smoothed ledge the vast expanse of Grymwood Forest spreads 
across the land like a verdant snow-covered carpet. Caught in the thermal 
air flows that rush down from the Teeth of Shartan, hawks and eagles,
your cousins of the sky, glide gracefully amongst the treetops. This 
ledge marks the furthest area that can be climbed at this spot of the
mountains. A deep sense of reverence fills the ground here, emanating 
from the circle of smoothed boulders that ring a jagged hole in the 
rocky ground. Perfectly straight cracks race outwards from the hole, 
like the spokes of a wheel, and disappear as they reach the boulders. 
A large opening in the mountain wall offers entrance to a dark cave.
*DESCRIPTION_END
