NUMBER 2246
NAME Cave of Smoke
ASTRAL
CALL 33
PARTIAL_DARKNESS
*DESCRIPTION_START
Tendrils of wispy, strangely-colored smoke emanate from long jagged cracks in the walls and floor of this small, rough-hewn cave. The smoke obscures vision and smells faintly of something mystical. The cavern continues downwards through a large hole.
*DESCRIPTION_END
ITEM 1 79 val2=2247
ITEM 0 72 VAL2=2245
ITEM 9 693
;newbie stuff
IFENTRY -1
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 6
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 15 	
    ECHO PLAYER A young wolfling cub lies in against the cool side of the cave. She looks up at you as you enter.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER She gives you a rather wolflish grin before she sniffs deeply.
    PLREVENT 2
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER She stands, and pads into a hole leading to the Cave of Time.
    EQUAL INTNUM6 7
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 7
    ECHO PLAYER You get the feeling there was more to learn from the pool. 
  ENDIF
  IFVAR INTNUM6 = 8
    EQUAL ROUNDTIME 60
    ECHO PLAYER A greying Elder She arrives before you. She sniffs you briefly, and then informs you, "One is only catching your scent. It is custom of our kind to sniff others in greeting."
    PLREVENT 3
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER The she gazes you up and down, nodding approvingly. "Now then, one would ask for your upmost attention. A wolflinng does not speak in public while in the shape of a wolf. It is very ill-mannered, and only the poorest bred wolflings do so. On the other hand, amongst our own kind, it is entirely acceptable."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER She continues, pausing briefly to scratch at an itch. "We are meat eaters of course, shunning fruit and other such silly things."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Now then, youngling, wolflings are diverse creatures as you saw. Most races are our friends and even allies. Humans and aelves especially. But the Mardhrel are not. Those of the dark skin are at the least, not to be trusted."
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER The Elder gets to her feet, and pads to the opening. She gazes back and almost smiles. "One thinks you are ready for the outer world. Remember we are Pack, and we are strong. Do not hesitate to call upon a pack mate for aid. We are currently ruled by a council of five. Sinjin, Mariella, Saxon, Stolar and Rion are they. They will be able to help and aid you in your chosen path. "
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    ECHO PLAYER "Remember always that we are the chosen of Earthmother, of Shemri. We are the bane of the werewolves. Let your claws grow long and your howl be heard throughout the lands." She steps through the opening and is gone.
    PLREVENT 4
    CONTPLREVENT
    NEWITEM -1 255 ADJ1=181 ADJ2=72
    NEWITEM -1 253 ADJ1=25 ADJ2=182
    NEWITEM -1 217 ADJ1=568 ADJ2=410
    ECHO PLAYER You realize you have recieved several articles of clothing.    
    EQUAL INTNUM6 10
    ECHO PLAYER You blink, and find yourself arrived at the gates of Fayd.
    MOVE 201
    AFFECT 201
    ECHO OTHERS %N arrives.
    AFFECT 2246
  ENDIF
ENDIF
IFVERB SMELL -1
 IFVAR WOLFFORM = 1
  EQUAL ROUNDTIME 5
  ECHO PLAYER You feel a heady rush of exhilaration as your mind expands and opens...
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO PLAYER The smoke seems to clear your head, and cleanse your spirit as it fills you.
  EQUAL FLAG4 47
 ENDIF
ENDIF
IFPREVERB TRANSFORM -1
 CLEARVERB
 ECHO PLAYER The Call is too strong here, the wolf blood races like fire through your veins...you decide to keep this form...
ENDIF
IFPREVERB GO 1
 IFVAR FLAG4 ! 47
  CLEARVERB
  ECHO PLAYER A wolfling elder emerges from the shadows to bar your way.
  ECHO OTHERS A wolfling elder emerges from the shadows to bar %n's way. 
  PLREVENT 1
  CONTPLREVENT
  ECHO ALL A wolfling elder growls, "You must cleanse your spirit before descending.
 ELSE
